# Global Language Foundation

See [AIPIFY_GLOBAL_LANGUAGE_FOUNDATION.md](../../AIPIFY_GLOBAL_LANGUAGE_FOUNDATION.md).

## Core languages (mandatory)

Every new module, Business Pack, Industry Pack, Knowledge Center section, FAQ section, email template, notification template, Companion interaction, workflow, and portal page must support:

| Code | Language |
|------|----------|
| `en` | English |
| `no` | Norwegian |
| `sv` | Swedish |
| `da` | Danish |
| `pl` | Polish |
| `uk` | Ukrainian |

## Rules

1. **No hardcoded UI strings** — translation keys only (`t("namespace.key")`).
2. **All six core locales** — add keys under `locales/{en,no,sv,da,pl,uk}/` for every new user-facing string.
3. **English is fallback** — `getDictionary()` merges `en` when a core locale key is missing; missing keys are incomplete work.
4. **Extensible** — additional locales (e.g. `es`, `de`, `fr`) use `EXTENDED_LOCALES` in `lib/i18n/config.ts`; never refactor keys to add languages.
5. **Shared keys** — Customer App, Platform Admin, portals, email, and desktop/mobile use the same key paths.
6. **KC & FAQ** — Knowledge Center articles and FAQ entries require all six core locale variants or structured locale blocks per KC standards.

## Code

- Core list: `CORE_LOCALES`, `CORE_LOCALE_LABELS`, `isCoreLocale()` in `lib/i18n/config.ts`
- Runtime: `getDictionary()`, `mergeDictionary()` — English baseline + locale overlay

## Scope

Mandatory before shipping any new customer-facing or operator-facing surface.
